Bumble bee tuna... I can't believe he's gone.

Hmm... interesting last couple of days. i swear two migraines in one day is... ugh. oh well, count my blessings right. had a midterm today after my lovely head ache day yesterday. don't know, don't know; could go either way. got an email saying the highest score was 33 out of 30... yah, not me.:) played some ball which was pretty fun. i have a 8 game winning streak on full court games going. pretty sweeet. then tonight we tried to go to archery night which was filled up. so we roller skated instead. rollerskating is really fun actually. i havent rollerskated for... like, what? ten plus years maybe. its like youre gliding! :P then we decided to play "fight club" and one of my friends tried to flip one of my other friends over her back. she landed on her neck and i went running to the first aide station hearing gasps and "i.. can't breath". pretty flippin scary. glad she's alright. then some of us played settlers for a while and i won for the first time, but before that ash called me which was fun. i wanna go home.

1. Grab the nearest book.
2. Open the book to page 23.
3. Find the fifth sentence.
4. Post the text of the sentence in your journal...along with these instructions.

The Magician's Nephew

"No great wisdom can be reached without sacrifice. But the idea of my going myself is ridiculous. It's like asking a general to fight as a common soldier. Supposing I got killed, what would become of my life's work?"

Ok... so i put up a few more than one sentence. i thought it was interesting...

so i went out last night for my friends bday party. the restaurant was really dark, i got the wrong pizza, it had chicken on it, and of course i just so happen to be a vegetarian and take a bite. :( boooooH! never going back to that crappy place. gosh. too bad i didnt get the free dessert like the dude whos pizza it was. 

on the other hand, my midterm went decently, although i did have a dream last night about totally being screwed by a midterm. lets pray that never happens. 

it feels like christmas time here. so friggin cold. went to uVillage and there are all these people that have money buying stuff. commercialism, capitalism, money.. it all sucks major.

oh and cars are dumb.

looks like the curse might end soon. that is if the sox can win the world series after kicking the yankees butts like everybody should. so awesome. watching the last out right now... hopefully. dang, batter is walked. poo.

got midterm on friday. not feeling like studying too hard. i mean how hard can one study for geography?? even if it is the "sciencey" geography.

i got a pin yesterday from a friend that reads something like  "Asian Americans and Pacific Islanders for Kerry Edwards". OOHYAH! REDSOX WIN! REDSOX WIN!! anyway, so yah the pin is now on my backpack. its the awesomist.

i noticed today that i support freakin big business alot. i'm like a walking billboard. not sure how i feel about that. eh well. i guess i should start studying geo. ph.....

it was good to go home this weekend, spend time with my 'rents and friends. got to see alot of my lovely girl friends on sunday. i miss them. :) oh i have an awesome idea. briana, britt, etc. (i.e., whoever wants to come) you should visit me on the weekend that they do the salsa night here. that would be so tight. i'll have to figure out when that is... 

something must have happened over the weekend cause when i got back it was suddenly so cold and alot of the leaves have fallen to become a noisy yellow carpet on the ground. here comes winter i guess. :( well i gotta catch up on homework now.

Man oh man, what to do?... i guess i should memorize more characters. blah... i think i will try to get chris to play some ping pong tonight. work on my mad ball mashing skillz. cause girls like guys with good skillz yah know? knumbchuck skillz... :P

My left middle finger is swollen and slightly purplish. Basketball is a dangerous sport. Hey, people of LiveJournal, please keep the Evans family in your prayers.

I do believe I have been in college FOREVER. already slipped into the rut of taking naps. i wonder if i would have more time to do nothing with no language... eh, its the most interesting class, so oh well. i enjoy the liberal arts education this quarter. going from chinese to physical geography, to music, to mythology makes things interestingly diverse. gosh... there is this girl that visits my neighbor like every night and has to laugh all the time. AAAHHHHH! "ehhahahaha---ehahahha..." shut up! phh... oh my. i guess i should study more. :(
Oh yes, the gangsta that is me. it must be a gift that i haven't unwrapped and given to myself yet... eh well, on to the gangsta music theory homework. word.

time to brag. i grabbed my first birdie today! for those golf illiterate (sp? HAHA!) that means one under par! on a par four ripped a drive into the rough, put a nine iron on the green. and put it in. no one needs to know that i got an eight on the next hole! shhhh... :) oh golf, you tease me so. i guess thats why i keep coming back. sucker.

worked for my grandparents alot today. heading to n.h. tomorrow, then off tuesday for home. watched the usa guys suck at bball against puerto rico. sad sad day. i guess i am happy to be coming home. been out on the atlantic side a while now. but its been good times. b.g. here i come... in two days.

yeah for going home. yeah for easter. yeah for easter eggs. yeah for sunny weather. yeah for sleep. yeah for the big g upstairs.

alrighty, now that i've already started to forget lots of SB, time to get down what i do remember... let's see, i went to eternal sunshine on wednesday with bri, britt, christina, lori, ryan. good movie, just we missed the first part so didnt get it totally but was a really good movie anyway. we tried to go to a switchfoot concert but didnt happen. *and insert something i forgot* after the movie we some of us headed to st clairs and got honey to watch, aight movie i suppose if you like the corny, feel good types. not my fav but then we danced to an instructional vid on the dvd based on a move from the movie. good times... withey saying "and 5, 6, 7, 8..." haha. though the dance seems kinda boybandish to me. must be cause i'm white. ha! *and back to what i wrote before* next day took my mom to the airport and got my jordans! woohoo. played vid games with lil zig like usual. friday friday... went out to ladykillers with dad and jeff. hung out with britt and ash. played taboo and uno!!! i suck at uno. went to church. went on a hike. it was good. dirty and good. MUDdY! then hit a blazer game, 15 from the front baby! kill those sonics good. in OT. man theo is the man. damon's doin hot too. ooh, got some free blaza posters. hooked jeff up with one. prob gonna give z one too. hung out after with ash and britt. good times. stalled in the driveway!! ha... with the ladies too. very smooth. but ash is used to that ;) packed this morning then crammed what i could into the dow's car. ah yes. played ball for a couple today. rusty. not good. man i gotta clean up my room. still havent unpacked. i will not be lazy this quarter.

Wooohooo for spring break. just thought i would jot down some memories from the weekend before they slip my mind. MEMORIES! ALL ALONE IN THE MOONLIG... er... yah: played video games with jeff alot. drew tattoos! ashley, britt, and bri were my victims, and i was britt's lol. the blanket!! HAHAHA! hmm.. watched my huskies loose to UAB, not good.  but the KFC was excellent. went to the beach on saturday: playin ball, wrestlin britt, chuck's crying, ryan buried under the mermaid (and britt, his tent... not good. LOL), the crazy rainbowish halo around the sun. longboarded in the dark outside the st clairs. getting sick on sunday, played bball on sunday night. hung out today... i mean yesterday i guess now, and went to a blazer game. too bad we lost. gotta love ruben's monster posterization, oh and the rattles they handed out. i will cherish that thing forever. anyway, about time for sleep. oh how i love sleep. oh got more of my grades... yah for bumpin up the chinese grade. and i'm off...

*HUGS* TOTAL! give udub_uber_alles more *HUGS*

its so happy. i getta go home tomorrow! see my buds. not have school. see my parents. sleep in. buy clothes that fit. WOOOHOOO! so what did i do taday...? well i had no finals. went with z to the train cause he hadn't done it before. while we were down in international district went to owajimaya's. got the crazy asian small ass yogurtish drinks. gotta love em. came back... went to the gym eventually. stayed for about three hours. stupid crazy asian guy running into me and knocking the wind outa me. still hurts to breath deep. oh and stupid guy that elbowed me in the lip. damn, my pretty boy level just went down like a million notches. gotta work on getting it above zero. HA! anywho, i'll see a bunch of you peeps in just a lil bit. WOOHOOO!
